{"title":"Canyon Lux & Exceed mountain bikes go faster, lighter for 2022 XC race season","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/29/canyon-lux-exceed-mountain-bikes-go-faster-lighter-for-2022-xc-race-season/","date":1632911588000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054322/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Emily-Batty-One-World-Val-di-Sole-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Lux short travel carbon XC full-suspension bike,\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054322/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Emily-Batty-One-World-Val-di-Sole-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054322/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Emily-Batty-One-World-Val-di-Sole-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054322/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Emily-Batty-One-World-Val-di-Sole-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054322/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Emily-Batty-One-World-Val-di-Sole-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054322/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Emily-Batty-One-World-Val-di-Sole-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054322/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Emily-Batty-One-World-Val-di-Sole.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-273009\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Ridden to several World, European, National Championship &amp; World Cup wins this year, Canyon is giving their full-suspension Lux &amp; hardtail Exceed XC mountain bikes a facelift and spec boost for the 2022 race season. Neither frame itself has changed since the Exceed debuted its <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/18/canyon-spins-unicorn-hair-into-their-lightest-hardtail-ever-with-new-exceed-xc-race-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">superlight carbon</a> Canyon Factory Racing option last summer. But now that the Lux has its own Trail sibling, both cross-country bikes can focus on racing with short XC-tuned travel, aggressive race geometry, and lighter weight component builds.</p><h2>2022 Canyon Lux short travel carbon XC full-suspension bike</h2><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rUUTx44vlDs?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>Built for proper technical World Cup Cross-Country MTB racing – where the likes of Mathieu van der Poel, Emily Batty, Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado &amp; many more XC pros have put it through the paces – the Canyon Lux has been a perennial race favorite since its <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/07/02/first-rides-2019-canyon-lux-light-capable-100mm-travel-carbon-xc-mountain-bike/\">mid-2018 debut</a>. But now that a new longer travel <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/19/review-canyons-longer-lux-trail-bike-proves-a-little-more-suspension-goes-a-long-way/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">downcountry Lux Trail</a> is here, the original bike can dial back to its short-travel XC racing roots.</p><div id=\"attachment_273018\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054318/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Ceylin-del-Carmen-Alvarado-Worlds.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273018\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054318/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Ceylin-del-Carmen-Alvarado-Worlds.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Lux short travel carbon XC full-suspension bike, Ceylin del Carmen Alvarado\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054318/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Ceylin-del-Carmen-Alvarado-Worlds.jpg 1500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054318/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Ceylin-del-Carmen-Alvarado-Worlds-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054318/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Ceylin-del-Carmen-Alvarado-Worlds-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054318/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Ceylin-del-Carmen-Alvarado-Worlds-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054318/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_Ceylin-del-Carmen-Alvarado-Worlds-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273018\">all photos c. Canyon</p></div><p>For 2022, the carbon Lux pares back to 100mm of efficient front &amp; rear travel for all models with a cross-country race focus, and its most aggressive racing geometry. Plus, lighter weight standard components mean racers won’t need to swap out anything between Canyon’s consumer-direct delivery and the start line.</p><p>All XC fullies now come spec’d with rigid seatposts (droppers can still be added later), and the top-tier CF SLX models get handlebar remote lockouts for both shock &amp; forks.</p><div id=\"attachment_273017\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054313/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-7.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273017\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054313/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-7.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Lux short travel carbon XC full-suspension bike, CF SL 7\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1080\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054313/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-7.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054313/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-7-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054313/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-7-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054313/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-7-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054313/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-7-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054313/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-7-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273017\">2022 Canyon Lux CF SL 7</p></div><p>Four carbon Lux XC race bikes are available. The 2022 cross-country full-suspension ranges starts with the 3000€ Lux CF 6 with a complete Shimano SLX 1×12 groupset, Fox 32 Step Cast Performance fork, Float DPS Performance Elite Remote shock &amp; DT Swiss XR1900 alloy wheels. The 3700€ CF 7 steps up to an XT group &amp; Reynolds TR309c/289c XC carbon wheels.</p><div id=\"attachment_273016\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054309/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-team.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273016\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054309/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-team.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Lux short travel carbon XC full-suspension bike, CF SLX 9 Team\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054309/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-team.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054309/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-team-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054309/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-team-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054309/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-team-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054309/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-team-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054309/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-team-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273016\">2022 Canyon Lux CF SLX 9 Team</p></div><p>The slightly lighter 1662g carbon SLX frames build up into the 6200€ Lux CF SLX Team with Shimano XTR groupset, Fox Factory suspension, DT XRC 1200 carbon wheels, and one-piece carbon cockpits for a claimed 10.22kg total weight. And at the top, the 7000€ Lux CF SLX LTD gets an even lighter build of SRAM XX1 Eagle AXS, RockShox SID SL Ultimate fork, Deluxe Ultimate shock, and Reynolds Blacklabel XC carbon wheels at 10.16kg.</p><div id=\"attachment_273015\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054304/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-ltd.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273015\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054304/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-ltd.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Lux short travel carbon XC full-suspension bike, CF SLX 9 LTD\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054304/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-ltd.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054304/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-ltd-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054304/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-ltd-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054304/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-ltd-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054304/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-ltd-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29054304/2022-Canyon-Lux-short-travel-carbon-XC-full-suspension-bike_lux-cf-slx-9-ltd-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273015\">2022 Canyon Lux CF SLX 9 LTD</p></div><h2>2022 Canyon Exceed lightweight XC MTB hardtail</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062851/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_Emily-Batty.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062851/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_Emily-Batty.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Exceed lightweight XC MTB hardtail, Emily Batty\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062851/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_Emily-Batty.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062851/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_Emily-Batty-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062851/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_Emily-Batty-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062851/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_Emily-Batty-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062851/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_Emily-Batty-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062851/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_Emily-Batty-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p>There are even more options in the Exceed XC hardtail after the addition of a superlight <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/18/canyon-spins-unicorn-hair-into-their-lightest-hardtail-ever-with-new-exceed-xc-race-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Unicorn Hair</em> CFR</a> version last summer. Now the race-ready carbon hardtail comes in three layups – CF, CF SLX &amp; CFR – and all three levels available in team replica paint jobs for that pro racy look, and all with internal cable routing through the upper headset cup.</p><div id=\"attachment_273024\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062846/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-5.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273024\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062846/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-5.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Exceed lightweight XC MTB hardtail, CF 5\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1080\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062846/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-5.jpg 1800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062846/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-5-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062846/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-5-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062846/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-5-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062846/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-5-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062846/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-5-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273024\">2022 Canyon Exceed CF 5, coming soon</p></div><p>Canyon says the Exceed family highlight is their entry-level CF carbon frame at a decently light 1312g with accessories (it is 477g heavier than the CFR frame, but you can get a complete CF bike for about 1/3 the price of a complete CFR build.)</p><div id=\"attachment_273023\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062841/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-6.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273023\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062841/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-6.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Exceed lightweight XC MTB hardtail, CF 6\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062841/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-6.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062841/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-6-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062841/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-6-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062841/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-6-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062841/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-6-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062841/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-6-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273023\">2022 Canyon Exceed CF 6</p></div><p>The most affordable current 2022 Exceed is now the CF 6 at 2400€ with Shimano SLX, a Fox Rhythm remote fork &amp; alloy DT wheels. But an even cheaper 1900€ CF 5 with Deore 1×12 &amp; a RockShox Recon fork is coming soon. There’s also a CF7 for 2900€ with GX Eagle &amp; a SID SL Select RL fork.</p><div id=\"attachment_273022\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062838/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-slx-9.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273022\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062838/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-slx-9.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Exceed lightweight XC MTB hardtail, CF SLX 9\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062838/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-slx-9.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062838/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-slx-9-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062838/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-slx-9-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062838/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-slx-9-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062838/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-slx-9-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062838/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cf-slx-9-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273022\">2022 Canyon Exceed CF SLX 9</p></div><p>Moving up to the CF SLX level (a 1015g frame) the Exceeds also move to a one-piece 322g carbon Canyon bar+stem cockpit, and get the 420g alloy DT Swiss <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/18/dt-swiss-d-232-alloy-mini-dropper-seatpost-gives-xc-racers-a-more-affordable-option/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">D232 mini dropper seatpost</a>. Pick from a 3700€ CF SLX 8 with XT &amp; Fox 32 SC Performance fork, or go for the 4700€ CF SLX 9 with wireless GX Eagle AXS and a Factory Fox fork, both with carbon DT Swiss XRC wheels.</p><div id=\"attachment_273021\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062834/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-team.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273021\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062834/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-team.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Exceed lightweight XC MTB hardtail, CFR Team\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062834/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-team.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062834/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-team-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062834/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-team-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062834/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-team-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062834/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-team-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062834/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-team-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273021\">2022 Canyon Exceed CFR Team</p></div><p>The top tier comes down to the 835g CFR carbon hardtail with two super-premium build options. Pick a Shimano mechanical build for 5800€ in the Exceed CFR Team with XTR, a Fox Factory fork, DT XRC 1200 carbon wheels and a flexing Canyon VCLS seatpost at 9kg. Or choose wireless SRAM in the 6700€ Exceed CFR LTD with XX1 Eagle AXS, a RockShox SID SL Ultimate RaceDay fork, Reynolds Blacklabel XC carbon wheels, and a carbon <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/23/dt-swiss-d-232-drops-lightweight-carbon-xc-dropper-seatpost-in-27-2-30-9mm/\">DT Swiss D 232 One</a> mini 60mm travel dropper.</p><div id=\"attachment_273020\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062829/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-ltd.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273020\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062829/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-ltd.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Canyon Exceed lightweight XC MTB hardtail, CFR LTD\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062829/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-ltd.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062829/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-ltd-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062829/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-ltd-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062829/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-ltd-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062829/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-ltd-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/29062829/2022-Canyon-Exceed-lightweight-XC-MTB-hardtail_cfr-ltd-1536x922.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273020\">2022 Canyon Exceed CFR LTD</p></div><p>Both updated 2022 Canyon Lux and Exceed XC mountain bike platforms are available now in select builds and sizes, with many ready to ship now direct to your doorstep.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.canyon.com/en-gb/mountain-bikes/cross-country-bikes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Canyon.com</a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"212764ae1f6bb0cf170f942c9e4ed7eca15e8b62ad8d7539b4ac6d9a4c25ce5b","category":"Cycling"}